In this article, President Barack Obama issues a proclamation in honor of Labor Day. He highlights the hard work and talent of American workers, emphasizing their role in building the country. The President recognizes the importance of organized labor in raising living standards and building the middle class. He acknowledges the ongoing fight to protect workers' rights and values, particularly the right to organize and collectively bargain. President Obama also acknowledges the challenges faced by many Americans, such as unemployment, and expresses his administration's commitment to promoting policies that get Americans back to work. He concludes by proclaiming September 5, 2011, as Labor Day and calls upon all public officials and people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities that acknowledge the contributions of working Americans and their families.